	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh..sorry...you are right...you did have chanters on your &quot;leave alone&quot; list<br><br>Against a PLD, I also agree, per a little more thought, that the LOH, against an SK, probably does NOT equate to killing him near twice, as he will have to use it far earlier than when he is very low on health, but I would never underestimate a PLD in PvP, especially a savvy one.&nbsp;&nbsp;They have a lot of nasty / annoying things they can do, like their fast cast stun spells, root, they can decently buff themselves, they have fast cast heal spells, they can blind you (against an SK, that isnt too killer, but its annoying nonetheless), etc.<br><br>And they are, for the most part, every bit as good a tank as an SK is.  Perhaps the PLD you have been fighting were &quot;piles?&quot;  =P<br><br>To be honest, however, Im not sure I agree with the lvl 49 or lvl 56 NEC pet &quot;cannot be ignored&quot; comment.  While I am far from a PvP expert, I have gotten into it twice with a NEC recently and both times just charged him (they both jumped me! it was my natural reaction!).  One time the guy LDed (duhh) and the other time the guy must have got caught in between casting a few times becuase I just beat him to a pulp.  I even got (if memory serves) 2 DoTs on him with his pet beating on me.  I just chased him around the arena like a bull and tapped him at the end to finish him off.<br><br>I guess I feel confident that I will plaster the NEC before his pet plasters me, but, as stated below, you dont have to ignore the pet altogether.  Nowadays, post PoP that is, I would probably just festering darkness the pet and laugh as he is left in the dust.  A smart NEC, however, will probably go stand next to his pet (dispell is another option), but now I have him where I want him; in (somewhat) melee range.<br><br>A hybrid to me will always have an advantage in PvP, as they will always have something to fall back on.  A caster, any caster, CAN always present problems, but if resisted, he is essentially doomed.  A melee only class is just too limited without the aid of spells to support his fighting to hang in the end.<br><br>Ill take the hybrid in PvP, especially the SK or PLD.  <br><br>Note that there are some classes, like a bard or shaman, who are just in their own little world.  I have never gotten into it with them personally but have read many accounts from others, ranging from &quot;dont ever mess with them!&quot; to &quot;they are easy!&quot;  I dont know, but Im not all too excited about tangling with them.  They would annoy me too much.  =)<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
