	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10382413499462><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10382413499462>RE: PvP?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10382413499462#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>217 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 25th 11:45 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh, the NEC has SEVEN levels on you; this isnt going to be an easy fight.<br><br>Although SKs arent exactly the #1 desired class at say raids or something, we definitely DO rock in the PvP world.&nbsp;&nbsp;While I certainly wouldnt make the claim that SKs are the best, they definintely are amongst the best.  Keep in mind, however, this advice comes from a non-PvP expert.<br><br>The first thing I would do is put on all the resist gear I could.  He isnt going to melee the crap out of you (well, his pet will try, but..), so you will want to resist as many spells as you can.  Resisting spells is the bane of a casters existence&amp;#8230;<br><br>Additionally, it is inconceivable to me that a NEC isnt going to send his pet in after you almost immediately, so you need to know what you are going to do.<br><br>You basically have 4 choices:<br><br>1. Ignore the pet altogether and just charge the NEC<br><br>2.  Fear his pet (if possible)<br><br>3.  Snare his pet, then charge the NEC, leaving the pet in the dust.<br><br>4.  Have your pet attack his pet.  His pet will demolish yours, but you have the life of your pet to play mono-a-mono with the NEC (his pet will not back down from something that is attacking it)<br><br>Im fairly certain that you cant fear another player in PvP, but Im not certain if you can target and fear a pet or not.  If you cant target the pet for fear, snaring his pet works just as well.<br><br>A NEC will clearly NOT long to stand toe-to-toe with you, so he will either try and snare/root you or shadow step away from you.  Those really are his only choices, lest you will catch him and beat the living tar out of him.  As an SK, however, you also can snare, and I would DEFINITELY have engulfing and / or dooming up (probably dooming, but if you are worried about cast time or running OOM, then engulfing).  If you are able to snare him, and he doesnt snare you, prepare for some fun, because all he can now do is SS away from you, but that is random and he surely will teleport close to you more than once, allowing you to smack the crap out of him.<br><br>If I were a NEC, I would have something like this as my spell line-up:<br><br>2 best DoTs<br>highest lifetap<br>screaming terror<br>Cancel magic<br>harmshield<br>gate<br>shadow step<br><br>As a lvl 50 SK, my spell lineup would be as follows:<br><br>Dooming darkness<br>Lifedraw (although you should get to 51 so you can go into battle with Siphon Life)<br>Heart Flutter<br>Heat Blood<br>Spear of Pain<br>Cancel magic<br>Life leech if you got it or maybe even siphon strength or wave of enfeeblement (with the combination of heart flutter, you can try and weight encumber him, thereby &amp;#8220;snaring&amp;#8221; him; hell, you can even load all three and see of that works)<br><br>Try and put a &amp;#8220;clicky&amp;#8221; or two into you 2 top buff slots, then remove them just prior to fighting, so you can cancel magic any nasty dots he gets on you.  I generally charge straight ahead and hope the dots don&amp;#8217;t kill me first, but that would make a good defensive move nonetheless.<br><br>NECs don&amp;#8217;t have a good defense in melee and certainly don&amp;#8217;t have a lot of HP.  If you do manage to get snared / rooted, I would make sure that you land your DoTs, smack him with some taps when needed, and mostly bomb away with Spear of Pain.  Granted, it will be nerfed in PvP, but a 57 NEC getting hit for ~200 pts a pop should make a noticeable decrease in his HP.<br><br>Snare against a class that cannot SS (or the equivalent) is a fight-turning spell.  A NEC, however, can SS, but its still a NICE DoT to have on him.  I would definitely try and land snare on him.  That will make him nervous regardless.<br><br>Always remember your HT.  Once his gets to approx 40% of his health, BAM! HT him and watch as his charred remains sizzle at your feet&amp;#8230;.<br><br>The fight would be vastly different if you were lvl 57.  Id be interested to see him talk trash to a comparably equipped lvl 57 SK, to say nothing about an SK that is seven levels higher than he is.  I can assure you that, all things equal, a lvl 64 SK is almost always going to own a lvl 57 NEC.<br><br>Luna<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
