	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 5th 9:22 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I just realized that I haven't been super helpful. The techniques described above are good. Frankly, I'm not certain this particular battle is winable given the 7 level difference between the SK and Necro. However, having played both an SK and a Necro PvP, the strategy I would recommend is the following:<br>1) Prep by putting up as many clicky buffs as possible. Then, put up Mental Corruption, Grim Aura and Deadeye. During the fight, you'll need Boil Blood, Cancel Magic, Siphon Life, Spear of Pain/Plague, Heart Flutter, Fear and Shadow Step. <br>Make sure you are equiped with a shield and a 1hander. You MUST bash to interrupt his casting. Failure to do this and you are dead.<br>2) Start by sending your pet after the Necro and Rush him, he's either going to dispel you or snare you. Try to close the distance between him and you before he gets the first spell off ignoring his pet completely. If you manage this, hit the bash button every time he starts to cast.<br>3) By sending your pet and rushing, you give him two targets to deal with - at 49+, your pet does significant melee damage to a caster, so it can't be ignored for long. If he ShadowSteps, follow your pet. If he's engaged on your pet, tell your pet to back off and his pet will lead you to him. Close the distance as quickly as possible and try to hit him again. If he lands snare, the melee game is pretty much over.<br>4) If/when snare hits you, cast your dot's and play like a Necro/caster. Cast, SS, etc. Your DoT's are weak, but he has very few HP's compared to you. Chain fear off his pet if it comes at you. <br>5) I've never lived long enough to try this, but see if you can dispell darkness. If so, rush him and nail him with a HT. If you landed Heat Blood and hit him a few times and he's at about 40%, he'll probably die quickly, or freak out and make mistakes.<br>6) Remember to Lifetap. You are tapping against the master, and I'm certain he has Bond of Death on you (Lifetap DOT for 720 hp's) by now, but every little bit helps. Stick to the faster casting 75 hp version and tap away.<br><br>Again, I don't know if this will work. I'm basically describing how I would do it if I had to do it all over again. I don't consider myself an expert, but I do want to be helpful. Hope there's something in here of use to someone.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
